76561198042220545,Recommended,262450,16760294,"Posted: 28 June, 2015",all,FatalCharm,"Do you like card games?  If so, then this relatively unknown gem is one that you need to add to your collection.  The game was so well-received that Mayday games (in conjunction with Stardock) made a physical version of the game that can be purchased at Amazon and other retailers.Dead Man's Draw is a pirate-themed  card game with an interesting rule-set that changes each game.  Each of the 10 suits has it's own unique 'ability'.  Additionally, players can choose up to two 'triats' each hand that invariably change the gameplay and adds to replay value.There are some things that the game could have done better.  The lack of multi-player is the biggest thing missing from the game.  Another thing that would have made the game even better would be a 'free-play' mode; the game is very structured -- which is great for learning the game -- but that 'structure' means that the game will decide who you play, in what order you play them, and any special rules for that particular game/hand.Dead Man's Draw is an entertaining card game that can be played for 5 minutes at a time or 5 hours at a time.  If you like cards and you see this on sale ... get it."
,Recommended,262450,9412194,"Posted: 10 March, 2014",all,gorpie,"If you like card games, definitely give this a shot.It has a unique deck, and each suit has unique properties.  Unlocking traits lets you extend the abilities of each suit.  The play is in tournament style, with each tournament having its own rules to make this an interesting game.  The nine different opponents you face also have their own play styles.The game is simple to learn, but your traits and the opponent traits, plus the tourney rules make the gameplay varied and not boring.EDIT: You don't get to simply pick your two favorite traits and stick with them for every game - the traits chosen by your opponent can nullify a trait you choose."
,Recommended,262450,9030751,"Posted: 9 February, 2014",all,Kejmur - AFK,"After hours and hours of playing this card game I need to say it's really well made. While I'm not a huge fan of pirate theme, it's still something I really enjoy playing and I don't think I'll ever get bored of it. For first I'll point out pros of this, because I need to point out few of them:A) Combination of really easy to learn mechanics combined with amount of strategies you may pull off with cards you have on your hand + traits. Traits is what make this so fun to play and yet allow you to be creative with your plays. Technically after tutorial you learn everything you need, while with each in-game tournament you learn new card combos and gain traits to use.B) The amount of gameplay which in-game tournaments provide you. Counting all cards when it goes to points ? No problem. You need to reach 50 points first ? Also in. You can't score more than 60 points while beating opponent in points ? In as well. The amount of possible modes to play in is just nice making each tournament pretty much different.C) Graphics and music are good combination here. For a simple game like this, I would say it fits really well.D) Still lots of room for improvements and new additions. The amount of cards is good, but not huge enough IMO to add few cards in-game without making it too complicated. There's also a possibility of new traits. In other words - this game has still more potential for improvement.E) Good AI which actually can not only count well (which is not as obvious in such games) but counter your strategies and eliminate/steal cards which are the main core of your strategy. I'm really happy with this as it makes game challenging.Although unfortunately I see few problems as well:A) Lack of multiplayer is outright unacceptable. I would really love to play this game against real players and outright test some traits and card combos against them, especially when this game has the perfect combination of simple mechanics and yet good amount of strategies and combos available to use. Please, do it. It's such a waste otherwise.B) Price is a bit too high for a card game like this, but I must admit I don't regret spending this money. But still, I would lower the price. Or I won't even bother mentioning this as a con as long as creators will add multiplayer option.C) While it is luck based (and I don't mind this, it adds additional thrill for example when one lucky pull saves you), but I think game favors AI a bit more than a player. But maybe that's me and I'm a bit biased. But still, you should still win more games than loose if you choose your cards and traits right.In other words I give this game 8/10 because of small cons and lack of multiplayer. I really recommend this game as it's fun, addicting and challenging, while you don't need to waste time learning complicated mechanics. I would give 9.5/10 with multiplayer, but without it - I can't. Still good buy and certainly not wasted money as long as you enjoy card games ;)."
