76561197995425192,Recommended,262450,9330705,"Posted: 3 March, 2014",all,Meanwhile,"One of the best casual card games I've played -- and I've played a lot of them! The deck consists of 10 suits of cards numbered 2 through 7, and your simple goal is to get the highest single card of each suit you can, with lower-ranked cards you collect functioning as backup for when (not if) your top card gets stolen.Each suit has a special ability tied ingeniously to its thematic element.  For example, swords allow you to steal and play a card from your opponent's hand, while anchors ""lock down"" all previous card in the current play to protect them from a bust. (A bust occurs if you draw a second card of an already-played suit in the same turn.)The artword could not be better, and there are tons of special abilities (""traits"") to unlock.  Achievements are gained by playing a series of tournaments using special rulesets (e.g., ""Swords and cannons target the lowest card of a suit instead of the highest"").  Even though it's a completely casual game, I find myself enjoying it for hours at a time.  If you like card games, you MUST get this one."
