,Not Recommended,262450,24519966,"Posted: 25 July, 2016",all,KrudlerTheHorse,"TL;DR Very simplistic card game requiring almost no skillThis is a very basic card game where the objective is to form a better hand than the computer opponent.  You form hands by taking turns drawing from a deck, each turn ending when you/AI collect the cards drawn, or bust by uncovering two cards of the same suit.  When the deck is depleted, the round is over and the winner is the player who has the better hand.There you have it.  If that sounds interesting, go ahead, but that's all you'll be getting.Sure, there are special card abilities and other razz-a-matazz to make the game seem more interesting but those don't change the fact that it's basically a simplistic luck-based game with a little bit of decision-making thrown in to make it seem like your skill factors into it.Good graphics, good presentation, good user interface and reasonably smart AI, yet stupid enough to make conspicuously bone-headed decisions, which breaks immersion.Maybe I've played too many card games in my life, or maybe I've programmed too many, but this game doesn't offer me what I want which is a skill-based card game with a little luck thrown in.  Instead this is a luck-based game with a little skill required."
