,Recommended,262450,18731755,"Posted: 28 October, 2015",all,Jonman[GWJ],"Dead Man's Draw is a slick and polished head-to-head card game, played against an AI opponent. The rule-set is initially very simple, with more rules and features introduced as the player progresses, providing a smooth introduction to the finer points of playing the game.As with many card games, luck plays an enormous factor in your success or failure, but there is also a significant degree of skill that can be applied to influence the outcome of a game.A single round of the game takes only a minute or two, meaning that this is an excellent ""filler game"" for when you only have 5 minutes to play something quickly. That said, there's a reasonably long campaign-style progression, which continually offers new opponents with various abilities and tweaks to the rules to keep things interesting over many hours of gameplay, and it's easy to get sucked into ""one more round"".Overall, it's a splendid little game."
